<ol>
  <li>Place the raspberries, cinnamon stick and lemon in a saucepan. Bring to the boil and mash the mixture. Boil for another 1-2 minutes, while stirring continuously.</li>
  <li>Add the sugar and bring the mixture to the boil for another 5 minutes.</li>
  <li>Pour into the jars and allow to cool overnight.</li>
</ol>
